  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page1_title" : "What is Futures Martingale?",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_label" : "Volatile Market/Short or Long/Advanced",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page1_paragraph1" : "Futures Martingale is a trading bot that can help users to reduce the average cost while having long or short trades in volatile markets.\nAfter selecting the long/short direction, you can set the parameters such as leverage and the amount of initial order to trade in the Futures markets. If prices move against your position, Futures Martingale bot will increase investment to increase position, therefore reducing average cost. Once the market rebounds, the coins bought earlier will be sold at once to take profit. Compared to Spot Martingale, Futures Martingale supports long or short trading and customizable leverage, providing investors with more trading methods to gain profits.",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page2_title" : "Advantages of Futures Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page2_paragraph1" : "If you believe that a coin price will fluctuate in the medium and long term, you can choose the Futures DCA bot, which has following advantages:\n1. Long/Short: Futures Martingale bot supports long or short positions, applicable to both bullish and bearish users.\n2. Trade with Leverage: By trading with leverage, you can increase the capital efficiency and profitability. Applicable to different risk appetites.\n3. Customizable Parameters & Risk Control: You can customize the parameters according to your own needs to manage the risks.",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page3_title" : "How to trade with Futures Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page3_paragraph1" : "There are two methods:\n1. Follow a bot provider/Copy a backtesting bot: You can filter out top performers or backtesting bots in the Recommended section and follow a provider or copy a bot to trade.\n2. Customize your own bot: Based on your own judgment of the markets, you can choose to open a long/short position and then customize parameters such as leverage, amount of initial order and price deviation.\nTips: The more DCA orders and investment, the larger your position, the higher the risk of liquidation.",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page4_title" : "How to terminate Futures Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_futures_martingale_page4_paragraph1" : "You can terminate Futures Martingale at any time. Please note:\n1. Futures Martingale should be terminated timely when a coin has been in a one-sided market.\n2. Futures Martingale is suitable for medium to long-term volatile markets, so in the short term there may be floating losses as the price has not reversed yet. Please monitor the market trend to invest with caution.",
